title: Jordan Fredericks' dazzling touchdown 'definitely should be on ESPN'
text:
Tampa, Fla. â€” Syracuse freshman running back Jordan Fredericks may find himself on SportsCenter later tonight.
Ervin Philips certainly thinks he should be.
Fredericks' 30-yard touchdown in the third quarter didn't mean much in the end of a 45-24 loss at South Florida.
But his two-juke, one-spin and burst-of-acceleration scamper to pay dirt was a play to behold.
"That was sick," Philips said. "It definitely should be on ESPN."
Fredericks has been a key contributor for a Syracuse offense that has been much improved over the previous two seasons.
His touchdown scamper Saturday confirmed what many have noticed.
He just has an instinct to make plays.
"I faked the ball, really, and I just carried out my fake, and I just turned around and saw (Eric) Dungey in a scramble," Fredericks said. "He just checked down to me. After that I just thought about the end zone and just ran into it.
"Everything that happened just happened. It's all instinct."
